declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle *integer setters* (i.e., functions setting the values of integer
variables).
/---

# ....................{ SETTERS                            }....................
declare_function_with_stdin <<'/---'
void :set_int_to_int(string int_name, int number)

Set the value of the passed integer variable to the passed integer: e.g.,

.:set_int_to_int()
==========================================
[source]
------------------------------------------
>>> :int euler_gompertz
>>> :set_int_to_int euler_gompertz 59634736232319407434107849936927937
>>> output_string "${euler_gompertz}"
59634736232319407434107849936927937
------------------------------------------
==========================================
/---
function :set_int_to_int() {
    # Validate sanity.
    die_unless_args_2 'Expected one integer name and one integer.'
    :string int_name__siti="${1}" int__siti="${2}"
    :die_unless_var_integer "${int_name__siti}"
    die_unless_integer "${int__siti}"

    # Set such integer.
    noop ${(P)int_name__siti::=${int__siti}}
}

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
